

Another name for the Generation Y demographic group of contemporary youth, those born roughly after 1980.

They are also sometimes called Digital Millenials, because they became 20 in 2000 and grew up familiar with internet technology.


=Citation=

"Gen Y demographic, which is people born after 1982. We call them "mods" because of the way they modify and customize everything, from their cars with the spinners on the wheels to their unique cell phone ringtones to their MySpace accounts, none of which are exactly alike. They're configurable, customizable markets of one as consumers, and as adults they want to be independent from the beginning of their careers and never work for an established corporation."
(http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/jan2007/sb20070131_094012_page_2.htm)

